---
import DocPage from "../../components/DocPage.astro";
const cb =
  "bg-background-dark p-3 border-l-2 border-border text-foreground-dark text-xs mb-6 overflow-x-auto";
---

<DocPage title="Getting Started">
  <h1>Getting Started</h1>

  <p>
    TermSurf embeds web browsers inside your terminal. Type
    <code>web localhost:3000</code> and see your work without leaving the shell.
  </p>

  <h2>Install with Homebrew</h2>

  <p>The fastest way to install on macOS:</p>

  <pre
    class={cb}><code><span class="text-primary">brew</span> tap termsurf/termsurf
<span class="text-primary">brew</span> install --cask termsurf</code></pre>

  <p>
    This installs the TermSurf app to <code>/Applications/</code>, the
    <code>web</code> CLI to
    <code>/opt/homebrew/bin/</code>, and Roamium (Chromium engine) to
    <code>/opt/homebrew/opt/termsurf-roamium/</code>.
  </p>

  <p>
    To upgrade to a new version:
  </p>

  <pre
    class={cb}><code><span class="text-primary">brew</span> update && <span class="text-primary">brew</span> upgrade --cask termsurf</code></pre>

  <h2>Build from Source</h2>

  <p>
    For development or if you want to build from source. Requires macOS, the
    <a href="https://www.rust-lang.org/tools/install">Rust toolchain</a>, and
    a Chromium build (~100 GB disk space).
  </p>

  <h3>Clone</h3>

  <pre
    class={cb}><code><span class="text-primary">git</span> clone <span class="text-success">https://github.com/termsurf/termsurf.git</span>
<span class="text-primary">cd</span> termsurf</code></pre>

  <h2>Build</h2>

  <p>
    Build all components (Chromium, Roamium, Ghostboard, and the <code>web</code>
    TUI) with:
  </p>

  <pre
    class={cb}><code><span class="text-primary">scripts/build.sh</span> all --release</code></pre>

  <p>Or build components individually:</p>

  <pre
    class={cb}><code><span class="text-primary">scripts/build.sh</span> chromium --release   <span class="text-muted"># Chromium + libtermsurf_chromium</span>
<span class="text-primary">scripts/build.sh</span> roamium --release    <span class="text-muted"># Roamium (Chromium engine binary)</span>
<span class="text-primary">scripts/build.sh</span> ghostboard --release <span class="text-muted"># TermSurf GUI</span>
<span class="text-primary">scripts/build.sh</span> webtui --release     <span class="text-muted"># web TUI</span></code></pre>

  <h2>Install</h2>

  <pre
    class={cb}><code><span class="text-primary">sudo</span> scripts/install.sh all</code></pre>

  <p>This installs:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>TermSurf</strong> to <code>/Applications/TermSurf.app</code></li>
    <li><strong>Roamium</strong> + Chromium dylibs to <code>/opt/homebrew/opt/termsurf-roamium/</code></li>
    <li><strong>web</strong> TUI to <code>/usr/local/bin/web</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Usage</h2>

  <p>Launch TermSurf:</p>

  <pre
    class={cb}><code><span class="text-primary">open</span> <span class="text-success">"/Applications/TermSurf.app"</span></code></pre>

  <p>In any TermSurf pane, open a browser:</p>

  <pre
    class={cb}><code><span class="text-primary">web</span> ryanxcharles.com</code></pre>

  <p>
    The browser renders inline, in the same pane. Use <code>Esc</code> to switch
    from Browse mode to Control mode. Use <code>Enter</code> to switch back.
    See <a href="/docs/components/webtui">Web TUI</a> for the full keybinding
    reference.
  </p>

  <h2>After macOS Updates</h2>

  <p>
    After a macOS update, rebuild Chromium. The Seatbelt sandbox APIs are tied to
    the macOS SDK version — a stale build will crash child processes.
  </p>

  <pre
    class={cb}><code><span class="text-primary">scripts/build.sh</span> chromium --clean
<span class="text-primary">scripts/build.sh</span> all --release
<span class="text-primary">sudo</span> scripts/install.sh all</code></pre>
</DocPage>
